column5: Too nice to sit indoors. Besides I was going cross-eyed making baits. So I grabbed my bag and some salties and spent the afternoon chasing panfish til dark. Nice mix of just about everything today.     And a fitting reward after a good day's fisking.
Sweet!  your reports are awesome.  Keep it up, it's only begun.
Nice Work Bruce. I took advantage of the weather to and got myself a nice little brown. Beautiful out there forsure
Yum yum. Made me drool all over my keyboard.
had another afternoon of feisty panfish All caught on an ice jig tipped with salties, then released.      Surprisingly, somebody else was catching all the WGSF.
Good mix of pannies. What's this? White bass? White perch?
A lot of them seem to like the taste of your left thumb. Ever think of using it as bait?
Actually, pike really like the taste of that thumb.
where was that? if you don't mind me asking.
Bruce, what are you using as a tartar sauce? looks good???
Looks like 1000 Islands dressing from here....not a bad idea
That there is 1000 Islands. I had run out of homemade. Home made is simple. 1 tbsp sweet relish, 2-3 tbsp salad dressing, pinch of cream of tartar (or leave it out)
looks great thanks for the tease
